Clarence B. MOORE, Appellant, v. A. C. ADERHOLD, Warden, United States Penitentiary, Atlanta, Georgia, Appellee. No. 7166. Circuit Court of Appeals, Fifth Circuit. Oct. 6, 1934. In forma pauperis. Clarence B. Moore, of Atlanta, Ga., in pro. per. H. T. Nichols, Sp. Atty., of Atlanta, Ga., for appellee.

Before BRYAN, HUTCHESON, and [WALKER, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

The judgment is affirmed.
